    "text": "Weather Information for Agriculture Act\n\nThis bill reauthorizes, revises, and establishes programs related to weather forecasting, monitoring, and research for agriculture.\n\nSpecifically, the bill reauthorizes through FY2028 the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s (NOAA's) National Integrated Drought Information System program, which coordinates drought monitoring and forecasting at the federal, tribal, state, and local levels.\n\nThe bill also (1) requires\u00a0NOAA to integrate advanced technology (e.g., artificial intelligence) into the program, and (2)\u00a0provides statutory authority for\u00a0the program's National Coordinated Soil Moisture Monitoring Network."
